DOCUMENT();    # This should be the first executable line in the problem.
loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'contextFraction.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

Context('Fraction');

$a = random(3, 5, 2);
$b = random(2, 3);
$c = $b - 1;
$d = random(2, 3);
$e = $b * $d;

$denom = lcm($a, $b, $e);

$x = Fraction($a * $c * $d, $a - $b * $d);

BEGIN_PGML
Solve the equation for [` x `]
[``` \frac{x}{[$a]} + \frac{[$c]}{[$b]} = \frac{x}{[$e]}```]
[` x = `] [_]{$x}
END_PGML

$a1  = $denom / $a;
$b1  = $denom * Fraction($c, $b);
$c1  = $denom / $e;
$ac1 = $a1 - $c1;
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Note that a common denominator (lcm) of all of the fractions is [$denom].  Multiply through by this:
[```
\begin{aligned}
 [$denom] \left( \frac{x}{[$a]} + \frac{[$c]}{[$b]} \right) & = [$denom] \cdot \frac{x}{[$e]} \\
 [$a1] x + [$b1] & = [$c1] x  \\
 [$ac1] x & = -[$b1] \\
 x & = - \frac{[$b1]}{[$ac1]} = [$x]
\end{aligned}
```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
